{
  "text": "In the Preprocessing stage, the system gets all available versions and metadata using the Dropbox API 1 , extracts content (both text and images) and other metadata using Apache Tika 2 ; and indexes the text using Apache Lucene 3 and images using LIRE [CITATION_1] . We implemented four Signal Detectors: 1) text similarity using Lucene; 2) metadata similarity using SimMetrics 4 ; 3) image similarity using LIRE [CITATION_2] ; 4) a simple domain-specific similarity, e.g. the exact match of the document name in the content.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "2087532",
    "[CITATION_2]": "2087532"
  },
  "bib_entries": {
    "2087532": {
      "title": "Lire: lucene image retrieval: an extensible java cbir library",
      "abstract": "LIRe (Lucene Image Retrieval) is a light weight open source Java library for content based image retrieval. It provides common and state of the art global image features and offers means for indexing and retrieval. Due to the fact that it is based on a light weight embedded text search engine, it can be integrated easily in applications without relying on a database server."
    }
  }
}